docs/next/lit/FUSE.sources.jsonl:1:{"id": "graphtoken-2024", "title": "Let Your Graph Do the Talking: Encoding Structured Data for LLMs", "venue": "arXiv (2402.05862)", "year": 2024, "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.05862", "claim": "GraphToken: a GNN trained against a frozen LLM emits soft tokens encoding graph structure. Abstract headline: 'across the board improvements - up to 73% points - on node, edge and graph-level tasks from the GraphQA benchmark' — the abstract does NOT name the baseline for the headline figure. Verified table-level fragments (Table 1): edge existence 0.738 vs soft-prompt 0.544; node degree 0.962 vs soft-prompt 0.098; cycle check 0.956 vs zero-shot 0.760. Trainable side: GNN encoder body 17K-199K params + ~11M-param projector. Envelope: algorithmic reasoning tasks over small synthetic graphs.", "fetched": "2026-07-11", "bib_verified": true, "venue_verified": false, "venue_note": "no peer-reviewed venue found; treat as arXiv", "claims_verified": "primary (abstract + Table 1 anchors)", "anchor": "abstract; Table 1; parameter counts per paper text (cross-checked against kb/eval/spot-audit-2026-07-09.json)", "audit_conflict": "KB record arxiv:2402.05862 is SPOT-REFUTED (kb/eval/spot-audit-2026-07-09.json) for assigning the 73-point headline to a soft-prompt baseline the paper does not support, and for an unsupported kv-injection tag. This ledger entry restates the headline baseline-free for that reason."}
docs/next/lit/FUSE.sources.jsonl:2:{"id": "gretriever-2024", "title": "G-Retriever: Retrieval-Augmented Generation for Textual Graph Understanding and Question Answering", "venue": "NeurIPS 2024", "year": 2024, "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.07630", "claim": "PCST subgraph retrieval + GNN soft prompt. Frozen-LLM vs prompt tuning (Table 3): ExplaGraphs 0.8516 vs 0.5763, SceneGraphs 0.8131 vs 0.6341, WebQSP Hit@1 70.49 vs 48.34 — the paper's 28.23-47.77% figures are RELATIVE improvements (absolute: +17.9 to +27.5 accuracy points; +22.15 Hit@1 points). With LoRA, deltas shrink to +1.95%/+11.74%/+10.44% (relative). WebQSP ablation (Hit@1 from 70.49): w/o graph encoder 54.62 (-22.51% relative, -15.87 pts); w/o textualized graph 56.96 (-19.19% relative, -13.53 pts) — the paper frames these as complementary components; COMPONENT CONTRIBUTION only, not causal use of topology (encoder also consumes textual node/edge attributes; no edge/label shuffle run). Retrieval cuts input tokens 83-99%. WebQSP graphs avg ~1,371 nodes.", "fetched": "2026-07-11", "bib_verified": true, "venue_verified": true, "venue_note": "confirmed at neurips.cc virtual poster page", "claims_verified": "primary (tables re-checked 2026-07-11 after independent review)", "anchor": "Table 3 (main results, relative-% rows); WebQSP ablation table; retrieval-efficiency table"}
