docs/next/lit/RULE.sources.jsonl:2:{"id":"crane-2025","title":"CRANE: Reasoning with constrained LLM generation","venue":"ICML","year":2025,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.09061","claim":"Theory: restricting output to an answer-only grammar diminishes reasoning; augmenting the grammar with carefully designed additional rules preserves reasoning while keeping constraints. Alternating unconstrained-reasoning/constrained-output gains up to 10pp accuracy on GSM-symbolic and FOLIO over both constrained and unconstrained baselines on the SAME model — an accuracy result, NOT resource-matched: Table 1 shows CRANE emits MORE tokens than unconstrained CoT in nearly every arm (e.g. Qwen2.5-1.5B 131.3 vs 128.97; R1-Distill-Qwen-7B 235.78 vs 212.24) plus constrained-decoder work.","locator":"Table 1 (GSM-Symbolic accuracy + avg tokens), FOLIO results section; re-checked at arxiv.org/html/2502.09061 2026-07-11","verified":true}
