docs/next/lit/SYS.sources.jsonl:2:{"id":"mlperf-inference-rules","title":"MLCommons MLPerf Inference Rules (inference_rules.adoc)","venue":"MLCommons GitHub (living rules; PINNED)","year":2026,"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mlcommons/inference_policies/c547732b539cb3a14cc5680597714c8c1df4cad0/inference_rules.adoc","locator":"scenarios table ('Scenario | Query Generation | Duration ...'), LoadGen operation section, and the Early Stopping Criterion appendix; commit c547732b539cb3a14cc5680597714c8c1df4cad0 (2026-07-07), re-verified 2026-07-11","claim":"Four scenarios with distinct query-issue semantics: SingleStream and MultiStream are CLOSED-LOOP ('LoadGen sends next query as soon as SUT completes the previous query'; 90%-ile resp. 99%-ile early-stopping latency estimate); Server is OPEN-LOOP (queries per a scheduled Poisson distribution; max Poisson throughput under latency bound); Offline sends all samples at once (throughput). 600 s minimum duration in every scenario. The 23,886-query figure is the rules' worked example (90th pctile @99% confidence/0.5% margin) and the minimum-query table is 'a suggested starting point', NOT a universal required sample size; the early-stopping criterion permits fewer processed queries at the penalty of a higher effective percentile and applies only once the minimum run duration is met ('When the minimum run duration is met...') — it never replaces the 600 s duration. LLM TTFT/TPOT pairs (Llama3.1-8B 2000/100 conversational + 500/30 interactive; Llama2-70B 2000/200 + 450/40; Mixtral-8x7B 2000/200); caching of queries/responses/activation-derived values prohibited, KV-cache within batch allowed; smallest LLM workload Llama3.1-8B","verified":true}
