docs/next/lit/SYS.sources.jsonl:14:{"id":"traeger-fsbench-tos2008","title":"A Nine Year Study of File System and Storage Benchmarking","venue":"ACM Transactions on Storage 4(2)","year":2008,"url":"https://www.fsl.cs.stonybrook.edu/docs/fsbench/fsbench.pdf","locator":"primary PDF re-read 2026-07-11: guidelines at Sec. 3.3-3.4 (pp. 5:7-5:8); survey compliance at Fig. 1 + Table I (pp. 5:9-5:10); authors' Auto-pilot config at p. 5:14","claim":"106 papers surveyed. Guidelines: disclose cache state; clear caches before EACH cold run (remount/purge/alloc-free); run each test several times with the NUMBER of runs determined from standard deviations or confidence levels (95% CIs recommended with half-width <5% of mean; Student's t below 30 runs) — NO fixed run count is prescribed; report full system state. 'At least ten times' was the authors' OWN Auto-pilot configuration, not a guideline. Survey found the majority of benchmarks did not specify run counts; per-conference MEDIAN run counts 1-3 (SOSP 1, FAST 1, OSDI 2, USENIX 3). CORRECTION 2026-07-11: an earlier revision of this entry misquoted a '>=10 runs' guideline and a 'median 7 runs' statistic (7 was a median count of reported system parameters, not runs)","verified":true}
