docs/next/lit/NTP.sources.jsonl:46:{"id":"scaling-flaws-2025","title":"Scaling Flaws of Verifier-Guided Search in Mathematical Reasoning","venue":"arXiv","year":2025,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.00271","claim":"Verifier-guided search with LEARNED verifiers (OVMs, PRMs) underperforms repeated sampling at large sample budgets across Mistral-7B/DeepSeekMath-7B on GSM8K/MATH - imperfect verifiers misrank and prune ALL valid paths, worst on hard/OOD items. Does NOT apply to sound verifiers on their covered slice; also verified in RAG.md and present in lit-KB (arxiv_2502.00271). Sound-checker loops fail by PLATEAU (data sparsity), learned-verifier loops fail by DECAY (precision).","verified":true}
