.beads/issues.jsonl:68:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-bww","title":"X1-grounding VERDICT=FAIL: NSM primes show no structural privilege on WordNet gloss graph","description":"Methodology-ladder X1 (child of 99a). Built WordNet-3.1 definition graph (83,253 single-word nodes, 1.18M edges post closed-class stoplist), computed Kernel(19,559)/Core(17,324)/Satellites per Harnad-2016. Corridor gates all PASS; T2 lemmatization audit cleared at 5% after Option-B closed-class stoplist (§9 Amendment 3). PRIMARY endpoint E-core FAIL: 50/51 primes ARE in the Core, but frequency-matched controls are too (null mean .9705 vs observed .9804), ER=1.01, p=0.58; E-kern also FAIL; sensitivity(usage) null agrees. Saturation/ceiling effect — Core is 88.6% of Kernel so membership is non-selective. NOT 'primes absent' — 'no detectable selectivity beyond definitional frequency'. Per pre-reg §6 binding: basis tilts to dictionary-derived core, NSM demoted to authoring vocabulary. Scope: this WordNet-gloss graph only, not NSM as linguistics. MinSet secondaries (E-ms/E-inv, finer ~1% grounding set) running detached N_MS=300, cannot change verdict but may annotate. Committed a136c5b, pushed.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-07-07T22:12:27Z","created_by":"ec2-user","updated_at":"2026-07-10T10:08:41Z","defer_until":"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z","labels":["parked"],"comments":[{"id":"019f4b80-3ea6-729c-9701-e7e4b76882dd","issue_id":"kernel-of-truth-bww","author":"kern-bd-graph","text":"Parked / off-active-path: X1-grounding VERDICT=FAIL (NSM primes show no structural privilege). E-core / tangential to the two feasibility theses; deferred off the ready frontier.","created_at":"2026-07-10T10:08:44Z"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":1}
.beads/issues.jsonl:69:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-bo6","title":"Order-invariant kernel reconciliation: dependency-aware re-derivation + bidirectional co-definition","description":"Concepts are minted in frequency-rank order, but definitional dependency does NOT follow frequency. A concept defined early (e.g. 'male') may be expressible more concisely/faithfully once a higher-level concept (e.g. 'person') is later available as a molecule — yet there is NO reconciliation pass that revisits earlier concepts to re-express them over later-minted higher-level concepts. Consequence: the kernel's conciseness AND canonicity depend on mint order, so two corpora built in different orders would differ. That contradicts the core claim of canonical, deterministic concept vectors — canonicity requires order-invariance (a fixpoint). Raised by @jeswr 2026-07-07. DEFERRED to a Claude-Fable session (design work; no Fable access now).","design":"Two coupled sub-problems. (1) Dependency-aware re-derivation: detect concepts whose explication shortens/improves by referencing a now-available higher-level molecule, and re-derive them. Content-addressing (urn:kot: = hash of explication) means re-derivation CHANGES the hash -\u003e need either (a) versioning/migration (old-\u003enew urn, rewrite referrers) or (b) settle-to-fixpoint-THEN-freeze: iterate re-derivation on mutable IDs to convergence, content-address only once stable. (2) Bidirectional/mutually-referential cycles: buy\u003c-\u003esell, parent\u003c-\u003echild, left\u003c-\u003eright, cause\u003c-\u003eeffect, borrow\u003c-\u003elend — each naturally defined via the other, but rank-order forces one first (bare primes) and the other gets the concise cross-ref. Options: co-definition per strongly-connected component, or a graph fixpoint. Procedure: build dependency graph; compute SCCs; topologically re-derive across SCCs, jointly solve within each; iterate to fixpoint; THEN content-address. Ties to E9: a reconciled kernel should be MORE order-invariant; measure vector drift pre/post.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Reconciliation pass yields an order-invariant settled corpus (same fixpoint regardless of mint order; verify with two random-order subsets). 2) Bidirectional pairs handled by co-definition, not first-mover verbosity. 3) Migration/versioning story for content-addresses. 4) Measure avg explication size + order-invariance before/after.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-07-07T17:48:47Z","created_by":"ec2-user","updated_at":"2026-07-07T17:48:47Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
