.beads/issues.jsonl:72:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-0kn","title":"X2-corpus FAIL 51/54: decoder drops optional SP slots / misorders referent intro under deep quote+op nesting (afraid, angry, sad)","notes":"Found by kernel-v0 corpus re-run (kernel-of-truth-138; poc/results/x2-kernel-v0-report.md). afraid: hard fail ERR_REF_NOT_INTRODUCED (ref 2 introduced out of order inside quote). angry: decoded AST drops \"quant\":\"SOME\" on an SP inside a quote (ok-but-wrong, minConfidence 0, step 'atomic-forced'). sad: drops an entire undergoer SP inside quote\u003eNOT\u003eCAN\u003eDO nesting. IDENTICAL failures with minimal (referenced-ids-only) and full-corpus cleanup lexicons =\u003e NOT lexicon interference; it is presence-detection SNR under deep quote nesting. All 18 reference-bearing concepts decode exactly; failures are the quote-re-anchored emotion trio. Synthetic X2 gate (720/720 full grid) never generates these shapes — extend the generator or add authored-corpus regression fixtures.\nRoot-caused (decode-spec-fix agent): SPEC RULING — the afraid RECORD IS LEGAL and the VALIDATOR IS RIGHT per gist §4.2 ('exactly one introducing occurrence'; 'a cdef:ref to an undeclared or not-yet-introduced index is a gate error'; 'Quote-local referents (bound inside a cdef:quoteClauses) scope to that quote'): ref 2 is declared, bound exactly once in quote clause 0, and every mention follows it inside the same quote. The decoder never disagreed about the RULE — it DROPPED the introducing SP (decoded HAPPEN.roles={}), then failed its own output's validation. Same mechanism as angry/sad: at quote\u003eop depth the true optional SP's presence signature (0.0335) sits BELOW pure-noise slots at the same depth (0.036-0.040) vs the 5-sigma gate 0.0552 — locally unseparable. FIX: decoder residual-completion phase (encoder/src/decoder.ts): after convergence, re-encode the decoded AST, subtract from v; missed content is then nearly the only residual content (measured 6-30x SNR at the missed sites: head 0.35-0.67, quant 0.33-0.68, bind ref:2 0.31, temporal op 0.46 vs noise ~0.02); probe every empty optional site there and accept a candidate only if the re-encoded edited clause explains the restored residual strictly better (exact matched-filter competition; phantoms cannot win). Encoder content-hash UNCHANGED (40e8c8ba...e2d10c); corpus UNCHANGED (no re-authoring, corpus hash stays f23f5211...); unit suite 38/38 (5 new regression tests incl. both validator ruling directions, encoder/test/corpus-regression.test.ts).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"decode-spec-fix","created_at":"2026-07-07T03:46:53Z","updated_at":"2026-07-07T04:23:13Z","started_at":"2026-07-07T03:58:00Z","closed_at":"2026-07-07T04:23:13Z","close_reason":"X2-corpus re-run PASS: minimal 54/54 AND full-corpus 54/54 exact (was 51/54 both; report x2-kernel-v0-report.md 2026-07-07T04:22Z). Ruling: afraid record LEGAL, validator right (gist §4.2); decoder fixed via residual-completion phase. Encoder content-hash unchanged (40e8c8ba...e2d10c), corpus untouched (hash f23f5211... unchanged, no X1-corpus re-run needed), unit suite 38/38. Follow-ups filed: synthetic-gate re-run/generator coverage (P2), substitution/removal completion (P3).","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
