.beads/issues.jsonl:80:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-j3iq","title":"b-cov-smol census BLOCKED: needs Fable instrument design (kappa_B over non-definitional SmolLM2-nine) before it can run","description":"Opus experiment-runner scoped b-cov-smol (docs/next/benchmark-evaluation-strategy.md sec.4 item 1) and STOPPED at the STEP-1 decision gate: it is NOT a mechanical reuse of existing tooling, so running it would require inventing coverage semantics (designer/Fable lane). No run performed, no files created, registry-check PASS.\n\nFINDING: b-cov-smol's headline deliverable is the per-benchmark kappa_B baseline (sec.10.1) via the two BINDING gates kappa_B^verify and kappa_B^engine. Neither has a reusable operationalization for externally-authored items, and 6 of the 9 benchmarks are non-definitional. `kernel_checkable` is today a build-time AUTHORED boolean (per-corpus stipulation), never a computed predicate over arbitrary item text; the only NL-\u003ekot-query leg (mapper/src/defineTemplates.ts) is CLOSED/definitional-only and onto-obo (biomedical-label) bound. So kappa_B^engine is plausibly ==0-by-construction for HellaSwag/WinoGrande/PiQA/GSM8K/ARC-Challenge/TriviaQA/CSQA (a MEASURED-null result Fable must characterize, not Opus).\n\nDESIGN QUESTIONS FOR FABLE (each blocks a MEASURED kappa_B cell):\n1. kappa_B^verify operationalization over externally-authored items: define the predicate deciding whether a canonical record backs a decidable proposition (P10) for an arbitrary external MCQ/open item — today only ever a per-corpus build-time stipulation.\n2. kappa_B^engine coverage of non-definitional items: how does expressibility-coverage apply to continuation/pronoun/affordance/arithmetic/reasoning/trivia items given the only NL-\u003equery leg is definitional+biomedical? Is kappa_B^engine ==0 by construction (report MEASURED-null) or is a new mapper leg in scope?\n3. sec.C5 uniqueness-filter operationalization for non-definitional items (docs/design-kot-query-define-op.md C5 defines it only for def-MMLU-style candidate-definition items).\n4. R-C lemma-touch \"supporting fact\" mapping for the 8 non-OpenBookQA benchmarks (only OpenBookQA has fact1; the field playing that role is unpinned elsewhere).\n5. SCOPE RECONCILIATION with bead kernel-of-truth-hu10 (OPEN, Opus): hu10's define-lane scopes the kappa_B^engine census to Tier-A DEFINITIONAL benchmarks only (WiC + biomedical def-MMLU + OpenBookQA control) and requires the define-op mapper leg + C5 filter implemented FIRST (design-kot-query-define-op sec.7.1). b-cov-smol (all nine) is a strict superset. Should b-cov-smol proceed only after hu10's define-lane lands, or is a separate instrument intended?\n6. (minor/moot until 1-4) per-benchmark sample n: split is pinned (sec.1.6 validation splits) but n is not; disclosed default (full split or 200 seed-pinned) is mechanical. TriviaQA licence now Apache-2.0 (reports/lit-eval-benchmarks.md) — confirm at freeze.\n\nCORROBORATION (3 independent): poc/define-op-census/RUN-LOG.md boundary-stop #2 (\"NOT buildable by adapting m0b\"); bead hu10 OPEN framing kappa_B^engine as an instrument to be built (definitional-scope); design-kot-query-define-op sec.7.1 places mapper leg + C5 as implementation prerequisites before sec.7.2 measurement.\n\nNEXT: route to Fable design wave after the current B'/registry writer frees (serialize — no concurrent Fable registry writer). Correction implied for benchmark-evaluation-strategy sec.4 (b-cov-smol is not the ~$0 no-gate mechanical first cut it is framed as).\n","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"fable","owner":"jeswrsolidserver@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-07-10T09:19:57Z","created_by":"Jesse Wright","updated_at":"2026-07-10T09:19:57Z","labels":["benchmark","design"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"kernel-of-truth-j3iq","depends_on_id":"kernel-of-truth-9gba","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-07-10T10:06:21Z","created_by":"kern-bd-graph","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"